project_descr:
Strengthening Institutional Response to Gender Based Violence in Serbia
funded by United Nations Trust Fund to End Violence against Women

outputs.output_descr:
The main aim of the project, fully in line with the National Strategy, is to achieve lasting change in the lives of women, their communities and the society as a whole by working to:  prevent violence from happening; and ensure all survivors of violence have access to care, support, justice and opportunities to rebuild their lives. In particular, the project will contribute to achieving the following outcomes in the field of ending violence against women, which correspond to strategic areas of the National Strategy:
